Disabling all managers in the Python category<pre><code>{
  "packageRules": [
    {
      "matchCategories": ["python"],
      "enabled": false
    }
  ]
}
</code></pre> <p>Alternatively, you can use <code>enabledManagers</code> to tell Renovate what package managers it can use.</p> Only use Renovate's npm package manager<pre><code>{
  "enabledManagers": ["npm"]
}
</code></pre>

Example of disabling a specific manager (gradle)<pre><code>{
  "gradle": {
    "enabled": false
  }
}
</code></pre> <p>Please check the list of supported managers.</p>

If most .yaml files in your repository are for Sveltos<pre><code>{
  "sveltos": {
    "managerFilePatterns": ["/\\.yaml$/"]
  }
}
</code></pre> Sveltos YAML files are in a sveltos/ directory<pre><code>{
  "sveltos": {
    "managerFilePatterns": ["/sveltos/.+\\.yaml$/"]
  }
}
</code></pre> One Sveltos file in a directory<pre><code>{
  "sveltos": {
    "managerFilePatterns": ["/^config/sveltos\\.yaml$/"]
  }
}
</code></pre>

Example config.js file<pre><code>module.exports = {
  endpoint: 'https://git-codecommit.us-east-1.amazonaws.com/',
  platform: 'codecommit',
  repositories: ['abc/def', 'abc/ghi'],
  username: 'ACCESS_KEY_ID_GOES_HERE',
  password: 'SECRET_ACCESS_KEY_GOES_HERE',
  token: 'AWS_SESSION_TOKEN_GOES_HERE',
  gitAuthor: 'your_email@domain',
  packageRules: [
    {
      matchPackageNames: ['package_name', 'package_name2'],
      enabled: false,
    },
  ],
};
</code></pre>
